para.itemizedlist:

    You now turn on Resteasy role-based security i.e. @RolesAllowed, by using the new resteasy.role.based.security context-param.


   @Wrapped is now on by default for lists and arrays and sets of JAXB objects.  You can also change the namepace and element names using this annotation.
.

@Wrapped no longer is enclosed in a resteasy namespace prefix nor uses the http://jboss.org/resteasy namespace.  Its just the default namespace.


@Wrapped JSON is now enclosed in a simple JSON array


 If you have the resteasy-jackson-provider-xxx.jar in your classpath, the Jackson JSON provider
     will be triggered.  This will screw up code that is dependent on the Jettison JAXB/JSon provider.
     If you had been using the Jettison JAXB/Json providers, you must either remove
     Jackson from your WEB-INF/lib or classpath, or use the @NoJackson annotation on your JAXB classes.
